Title: Black Hole Formation by Sine-Gordon Solitons in Two-dimensional Dilaton

GravityAuthors: Hak-Soo Shin and Kwang-Sup Soh

Comments: 11 pages, no figures, revtex

Journal-ref: Phys.Rev. D52 (1995) 981-984

The CGHS model of two-dimensional dilaton gravity coupled to a sine-Gordonmatter field is considered. The theory is exactly solvable classically, and thesolutions of a kink and two-kink type solitons are studied in connection withblack hole formation.